In a press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs, General McChrystal, and Ambassador Eikenberry discussed the efforts being made in Afghanistan. General McChrystal highlighted the growth and progress of the Afghan national army and police, as well as the ongoing efforts to secure the southern part of Afghanistan. Ambassador Eikenberry emphasized the importance of the civilian-military team and the need for Afghanistan to take the lead in its own security and governance. The briefing also touched on the issue of civilian casualties, the role of Iran in arming the Taliban, and the relationship between the US and Pakistan in combating terrorism. The discussion concluded with questions regarding President Karzai's visit to the US and the future of Afghanistan's government and reconciliation with the Taliban.